metadata.name: Timelines #10
metadata.description:
#fxhashturnsone - Happy Birthday fxhash!

Some days are busy and some are quiet.
Some weeks go fast and some go slow.
Some months are good, some are bad.
Here we are: talking about, looking at, making, collecting, buying, selling, trading and obsessing about generative crypto art.
Artists, collectors, artworks, opinions, trends, ideas; continuously overlapping, intertwining, influencing, burying, surfacing, remembering and forgetting.
We keep going, in search of the next.

This algorithm draws lines horizontally across the canvas.
There can be 12, 52 or 365 lines.
The lines can be straight, curvy, or both.
Straight lines can be angled or horizontal.
The line thickness can be random from 1-365, or all 12, 52 or 365 pts.
And there are 12 colour palettes.

Inspired by Sol LeWitt’s Wavy Brushstrokes work and the fxhash tweet prompting “365 editions” a week ago.

Follow me on twitter @fauxjebus

~—~—~—~—~—~—~—~—~

Features:
F - Fullscreen
S - Save image
2/4/6/8/0 - Change image resolution (press number key and then reload in live view)

metadata.name: Rearranged #63
metadata.description:
Rearranged is an invitation to engage in an exploration of aesthetics within the constraints of the generated token. 

Each piece has 4 layers. Each layer can be independently rotated by 90 degrees clockwise by clicking 1,2,3 or 4 on the keyboard. Some changes are subtle. Some are surprising. 

's' on the keyboard will scramble all of the rotations.
'r' will reset to the original artwork.

You are invited to: 
arrange a more aesthetically pleasing piece than the original;
scramble the artwork and use the number keys to return it to its original state;
work out which shapes have been erased from each layer.

And of course there is also a gorgeous gradient illusion made of solid-colour filled tessellating shapes. 

3 tessellations of varying sizes, 12 layouts with random elements, 14 palettes.

Made with p5.js.

metadata.name: Dencity #487
metadata.description:
Dencity is a generative art project inspired by aerial views of cities with a high density of buildings. Its perspective effect, its perfectly imprecise lines, its subtle textures and its very advanced level of detail give it the appearance of a hand-drawn work.

Behind the visible art (the image) hides another form of art, an extremely complex algorithm capable of calculating and drawing in 2D each variation of the Dencity project. To draw a variation, the algorithm notably takes around 3,000,000 to 20,000,000 random decisions based on the hash of the mint and draws around 800,000 to 4,000,000 lines to create all the strokes and texture effects.

Made with ❤️, code and p5js.

metadata.name: Punktwelt #280
metadata.description:
Continuing on the theme of color perception in Farbteiler, Punktwelt is an exploration of color interaction, projection and perceived depth, and the aesthetics of simple Boolean operations on form.

Each shape is the result of a single block, a rectangular cuboid, subjected to a series of Boolean subtractions with other blocks, and rendered in parallel projection, oblique or axonometric, in the abstract landscape of the Punktwelt.

Some have horizons, some have banded or striped backgrounds. The unnatural drawing order and chromatic differences of the individual faces sometimes yields illusory or paradoxical visual geometries.

Press ’s’ to save a png. Press ’4’ to export a high resolution png. Press ’8’ to export a very high resolution png. Press ’e’ to export an SVG file (may take some time and produce large files).

Aspect ratio variations are 4:5, 5:4, 2:3, 3:2 and 1:1.

Built in Javascript with p5.js, p5.svg and csg.js.

metadata.name: Magic Board #128
metadata.description:
When the ratio of two quantities is equal to the ratio of their sum to the larger quantity, there is a golden ratio in geometric patterns, and this property can create different geometric shapes.
The points are all randomly placed in each design, and the placement of these shapes together creates the impression of a geometric pattern based on random processing.
There is no end to these geometric patterns.
press 's' to save original size

metadata.name: RushGushBlush #63
metadata.description:
Let's celebrate #fxhashturnsone with a cascade of colors!

This is just my second release on fxhash and I couldn't be happier to dedicate this project, however simple, to this amazing community.

I could go on describing the details of this piece but honestly I just wanted to create something very colorful for the party, without putting too many hidden meanings! :)
(Or maybe not...)

Happy birthday fxhash!

---

80% of primary sales will be donated to the Processing Foundation and Save Pakistan.

---

There are 17 different palettes and 3 formats, hope you'll find a combination that makes you happy!
The texture might look weird in thumbnails, so I recommend opening the piece in full screen and/or download the png by pressing "s".

---

By Todemashi 2022
NFT License 2.0

### NOTES
Made with p5js.
This project uses fx(stdio) by @alt_escapism - https://altesc.art/stdio

metadata.name: Annum #139
metadata.description:
This project is being released in celebration of the 1 year aniversary of Achromat, my first release on fxhash. In addition to being inspired by Achromat, aspects of other previous projects have been incorporated. My deepest gratitude to all who have collected my work over the past year.

In live mode, add &size=<YOUR_PIXEL_SIZE> to change the pixel size of the image for export (Right click to save). For example, &size=4000 will set the width of the image to be 4000 pixels.

50% of primary sales go to Savepakistan.
